        <div id="InvoiceRequested">
            <div>
                <p>Now that we have requested the invoice from the dealership/documents from seller, we?re getting closer to organizing your loan documents, as previously discussed our loan products come with protection options. It?s now time for me to run through all the available options in detail and make sure you understand them all so you can make an informed decision on what package would suit you best. I have already sent you your features and benefits presentation, can you please bring this up?  </p>    
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>So first of all, let me just confirm, you have purchased (car details) for (purchase price) and we?re financing that over (loan term) with (residual) is this correct? (**We confirm this at the start to get them in the mode of saying ?yes?)</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><u><strong>GAP</strong></u></p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>The first thing to run through with you is GAP protection. Have you heard of the before? Do you know what that covers? It?s something that most people take out when they finance cars these days just because your insurance company will be de-valuing your car quicker than you?re paying back the finance. Because if your car is written off or stolen your insurance company only pays you out for the market value of your car, meaning if you do find yourself in the unfortunate situation of having your vehicle written off or stolen, once you?ve recovered from the shock of not having a car anymore you?ll usually be hit with a more painful shock being that not only do you not have a car anymore, but you still owe your bank or finance company an quantity of money because your insurance company has only partially paid out your loan. So the GAP protection will ensure for you that your loan will always be paid out. It covers the financial shortfall between what your insurance company pays you out, and the amount owing on the finance, up to a threshold of $X. In addition to that, you will also be provided $X cash to cover all your out of pocket expenses in the meantime such as car hire, taxis, comprehensive insurance excess, all those additional expenses. This will ensure you?re never off the road and not paying out of your own pocket to do so. Any questions in regard to the GAP protection.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><u><strong>LTI</strong></u></p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>The next thing to run through is loan protection. If you ever fall into a circumstance outside of your control that could impair your ability to repay the loan due to illness, injury, involuntary unemployment, divorce, driving restrictive medical condition, or international job transfer, you will initially have up to (3 or 6) months of loan payments covered for you while you get yourself back on your feet. If your still out of action beyond that period, then you will be provided the option of handing the car back. Any residual value between what the car is valued at at that point and what is owing on the finance would be covered, you will be relinquished from responsibility for the loan with no damage to your credit file if you exercise that option. Any questions in regard to loan protection?</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><u><strong>Platinum or diamond Warranty</strong></u></p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>The final level of protection we can provide is a warranty for your vehicle. Our warranty is what is called an exclusions warranty. An exclusions warranty covers absolutely everything on the car, only excluding wear and tear. Absolutely everything else on the car is completely covered, everything from your engine block all the way down to your power window motors. You have all parts and labor covered anywhere in Australia, and you even have lots of extras covered for you as well such as towing, or emergency accommodation if your car is immobilized away from home, you also have locksmith services covered for if you lose or break your key, or lock your key in your car, and if anything serious goes wrong with the car and your car is in the workshop for 30days or more, then the warranty will even cover your loan repayment for you whilst your car is off the road so it is a very comprehensive product. Any questions in regard to anything in the warranty?</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>So, as you can see from the presentation we offer 3 Packages, from fully-protected, Standard or Basic, which package would you like to proceed with?</p>
            </div>
